commit 867f46001c2add2045c120d1765e62cbde5778e6
Author: Sebastian Utz <su@rtme.net>
Date:   Mon Aug 26 11:51:36 2024 +0200

    Preserve the number of shards of existing partitions when altering the table
    
    Fixes a regression introduced by https://github.com/crate/crate/commit/111ffe166e523a4a5cd3278975772ce365112b64
    which falsely applied the current number of shards of the parititioned
    table to existing partitions when altering the table.
    This causes an exception as changing the number of shards is only
    possible by using the special `resize` operation.
    
    Fixes #16521.
    
    (cherry picked from commit 866a1a09b1accb2fb89fdb0e94b2f7f37d59b359)

